        g.adults,

        ei.PPI,
        ei.CPI,
        ei.Production_Index,
        ur.unemployment_rate,
        ur.date AS unemployment_rate_date,
        wd.datetime AS weather_datetime,
        wd.tempmax,
        wd.tempmin,
        wd.temp,
        wd.dew,
        wd.humidity,
        wd.precip,
        wd.snow,
        td.month AS tourism_month,
        td.tourists AS tourism_tourists
    FROM hotel_bookings hb
    LEFT JOIN guests g ON hb.booking_id = g.booking_id
    LEFT JOIN room_assignment ra ON hb.booking_id = ra.booking_id
    LEFT JOIN payment_info pi ON hb.booking_id = pi.booking_id
    LEFT JOIN booking_status bs ON hb.booking_id = bs.booking_id
    LEFT JOIN hotel_economic_link hel ON hb.booking_id = hel.booking_id
    LEFT JOIN economic_indicators ei ON hel.economic_indicator_id = ei.economic_id
    LEFT JOIN unemployment_rate ur ON ei.economic_id = ur.economic_indicator_id
    LEFT JOIN hotel_weather_link hwl ON hb.booking_id = hwl.booking_id
    LEFT JOIN weather_data wd ON hwl.weather_id = wd.weather_id
    LEFT JOIN hotel_tourism_link htl ON hb.booking_id = htl.booking_id
    LEFT JOIN tourism_data td ON htl.tourism_id = td.tourism_id;
"""

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve
def roc_curve_plot(y_test , pred_proba_c1):
    #   FPR, TPR   . 
    fprs , tprs , thresholds = roc_curve(y_test ,pred_proba_c1)

    # ROC Curve plot  . 
    plt.plot(fprs , tprs, label='ROC')
    #    . 
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--', label='Random', color='red')
  
    # FPR X  Scale 0.1  , X,Y     
    start, end = plt.xlim()
    plt.xticks(np.round(np.arange(start, end, 0.1),2))
    plt.xlim(0,1)
    plt.ylim(0,1)
    plt.xlabel('FPR( 1 - Sensitivity )')
    plt.ylabel('TPR( Recall )')
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
